         <div xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve" type="translation">
            <p>
               <milestone n="1" unit="line"/>We, Petronios, employee of the imperial estate, son
of Apollo, and Kyrapanton, his wife, to you, Menas,
archisymmachos of the divine house. <milestone n="9" rend="break" unit="line"/> We acknowledge
that we owe you on account of arrears of clothing
brought by us for Tebio, your wife, one onyx-coloured
cape, decorated with wheels, made of achae-cloth, <milestone n="22" rend="break" unit="line"/> and
one dress, and we shall deliver them to you in the
month of Mesore of the present fourth indiction with-
out delay. <milestone n="29" unit="line"/> Written on the 18th of the month of Tybi,
indiction 4.
(2nd hand) Written through me, Ioseph. <note>Translation: N. Gonis, P.Harr. 3 301</note>
            </p>
         </div>
